{"data":{"post":{"html":"<p>I recently came across this beautiful, evocative quote from Virginia Woolf's <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Waves\"><em>The Waves</em></a>:\n <br>\n<br>\n  </p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>\"There was a star riding through clouds one night, &#x26; I said to the star, 'Consume me'.\"  </p>\n</blockquote>\n<p> <br>\nI'm reminded of John Adams' <a href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/music/tomserviceblog/2014/mar/11/symphony-guide-john-adams-harmonielehre-tom-service\"><em>Harmonielehre</em></a>, which perfectly captures the feeling of this, particularly in the last movement:\n <br>\n\n <br>\n<br>\n<br>\n  </p>\n<div style=\"position:relative;padding-bottom:56.25%;padding-top:30px;height:0;overflow:hidden;\">\n  <iframe style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/3X-IUE_muQA\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\n</div>\n<p> <br>\n<br>\n<br>\nYou can read more about <em>Harmonielehre</em> in John Adams' own <a href=\"https://www.earbox.com/harmonielehre/\">piece description</a>.\n <br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<br>\n  </p>","frontmatter":{"title":"John Adams and Virginia Woolf","image":"blog/john-adams-virgina-woolf.jpg","description":"","date":"2019-02-27"}},"previous":null,"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/blog/synesthesia/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Synesthesia!"}},"image":null},"pageContext":{"post_slug":"/blog/john-adams-virgina-woolf/","img_path":"john-adams-virgina-woolf.jpg","prev_slug":null,"next_slug":"/blog/synesthesia/"}}